## Part 3: BC Labels (brief)

Biocultural Labels parallel TK Labels but focus on biodiversity and genetic resources. They include BC Provenance (BC P), BC Multiple Provenance (BC MP), BC Consent Verified (BC CV), BC Consent Non-Verified (BC CNV), BC Research (BC R), BC Non-Commercial (BC NC), BC Commercialization (BC C), BC Outreach (BC O), and BC Open to Collaboration (BC CB). Use these for entries where the maritime ecological knowledge dimension is primary. Full reference: [localcontexts.org/labels/biocultural-labels](https://localcontexts.org/labels/biocultural-labels/).

-----

## Part 4: How this connects to the toolkit modules

|Module                              |How Notices and Labels apply                                                                                                                                                  |
|------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|*Community Archive*               |Every item carries at least one Notice. Labels applied where community has authorised.                                                                                        |
|*Oral History Systems*            |Oral histories almost always carry TK Notice + likely TK Community Voice (TK CV) once Labels are live. Sacred recordings carry TK SS and are excluded from general processing.|
|*Memory Constellation Engine*     |Retrieval index filters out all items carrying TK SS, TK WR, TK MR, or TK CO. Items carrying TK CS surface with a content advisory.                                           |
|*Memory Map*                      |Place markers can carry TK Seasonal where rituals tied to a place have seasonal protocols.                                                                                    |
|*Ask Pulau Brani*                 |Refuses to surface or paraphrase anything carrying TK SS, TK WR, TK MR, or TK CO. For TK CS material, the chatbot uses community-approved framings only.                      |
|*Dialect and Vocabulary Archive*  |Sacred prayer language and ritual phrases carry TK SS or TK CS.                                                                                                               |
|*Advocacy and Public Storytelling*|Public-facing exports must carry TK Outreach (TK O) only, with explicit community sign-off recorded in the catalog entry.                                                     |
|*AI Heritage Lab*                 |Training datasets are filtered against the Label set. The AI Remix Studio respects every Label attached to source material.                                                   |

