## Part 5: Storing Notices and Labels in metadata

The toolkit stores Notices and Labels using the [DataCite-compatible](https://support.datacite.org/docs/local-contexts-notices-and-labels) rightsList pattern. Each Notice or Label entry includes:

- *identifier code* (e.g. TK-Notice, TK-A, BC-Notice)
- *identifier scheme* (always Local Contexts)
- *rights URI* (the Local Contexts Hub project URI generated when the Notice or Label is created on the Hub)
- *scheme URI* (always https://localcontexts.org)
- *template text* (default or customised)

See METADATA_SCHEMA.md for the JSON shape and catalog_entry_template.md for the human-readable form.
